FT  01 APR 93 / UK Company News: McLeod Russel
McLeod Russel has announced that its paints division, which comprises
Granyte Surface Coatings and Joseph Mason Paints, has acquired the technical
knowhow, order book and goodwill of the plastic wood and drum coatings
businesses of ICI Paints.
Consideration was Pounds 2.3m cash of which Pounds 1m will be payable in
instalments over the next two years. In 1992 the businesses had a combined
turnover of Pounds 3.8m.
